      • cleanupExecutor

        protected volatile java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService cleanupExecutor
        Executor used to close the filters.
        When close() is called, a task is queued in this executor to actually close the filters. When called, buildChain() cancels and clears that task, otherwise it throws.
        An internal, global executor is used if this field is null.

      • cleanupDelayMs

        protected volatile long cleanupDelayMs
        Delay, in milliseconds, of the cleanup task. Defaults to 15 seconds.
